HEADWORD: Three-lobed
<hw>Three"-lobed`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having three
lobes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Three-lobed leaf</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a leaf
divided into three parts, the sinuses extending not more than half way
to the middle, and either the parts of the sinuses being
rounded.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

